  "articles": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Building resilience through community empowerment",
      "slug": "resilience-community-empowerment",
      "description": "How local leadership nodes are transforming disaster response protocols in coastal Bangladesh.",
      "date": "2026-02-10",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593113630400-ea4288922497?q=80&w=1200",
      "author": { "name": "Ahmed Rahman", "role": "Field Coordinator" },
      "category": { "name": "Community Support" },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "__component": "shared.rich-text",
          "body": "<p>The optimization of community-led initiatives has reached a critical milestone. By decentralizing resource distribution and empowering local coordinators, we've reduced response latency by 45%.</p><p>Our field findings suggest that tactical empowerment is not just about resources, but about agency. When local stakeholders own the mission, impact is non-linear.</p>"
        },
        {
          "__component": "shared.quote",
          "body": "Empowerment is the ultimate load-balancer for social equity.",
          "author": "Ahmed Rahman"
        },
        {
          "__component": "shared.media",
          "file": { "url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1541185933-ef5d8ed016c2?q=80&w=1200" }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "title": "Sustainable solutions for clean water in rural areas",
      "slug": "sustainable-water-solutions",
      "description": "Deploying high-precision filtration nodes to ensure binary safe-water access in underserved sectors.",
      "date": "2026-02-12",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1541810270-3882d634017f?q=80&w=1200",
      "author": { "name": "Fatima Akter", "role": "Healthcare Lead" },
      "category": { "name": "Public Healthcare" },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "__component": "shared.rich-text",
          "body": "<p>Clean water is the fundamental infrastructure for community health. Our medical relief teams have successfully deployed 15 solar-powered filtration units in the Barisal sector.</p>"
        },
        {
          "__component": "shared.slider",
          "files": [
            { "url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594498257602-00x4f04f4721?q=80&w=800" },
            { "url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1488521787991-ed7bbaae773c?q=80&w=800" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "title": "Empowering next generation through digital literacy",
      "slug": "digital-literacy-empowerment",
      "description": "Upgrading rural education nodes with tactical digital toolkits and remote learning architectures.",
      "date": "2026-02-15",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1522202176988-66273c2fd55f?q=80&w=1200",
      "author": { "name": "Ayesha Siddique", "role": "Digital Trainer" },
      "category": { "name": "Global Education" },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "__component": "shared.rich-text",
          "body": "<p>Digital literacy is the master-key for economic mobility in the 2026 digital landscape. Our curriculum focuses on synchronizing basic computing with specialized node-development skills.</p>"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "faqs": [
    {
      "question": "How can I donate to Birdsfly Sangstha?",
      "answer": "You can donate through our secure online donation portal, bank transfer, or by visiting our office. We accept one-time and recurring donations. All donations are tax-deductible and you will receive a receipt for your records.",
      "category": "Donations",
      "order": 1,
      "serial": "FAQ-001"
    },
    {
      "question": "Are my donations tax-deductible?",
      "answer": "Yes, Birdsfly Sangstha is a registered non-profit organization. All donations are tax-deductible under applicable tax laws. You will receive a donation receipt that can be used for tax purposes.",
      "category": "Donations",
      "order": 2,
      "serial": "FAQ-002"
    },
    {
      "question": "How can I volunteer with your organization?",
      "answer": "We welcome volunteers! You can apply through our volunteer registration form on the website. We offer various opportunities including field work, administrative support, event coordination, and professional skills-based volunteering.",
      "category": "Volunteering",
      "order": 3,
      "serial": "FAQ-003"
    },
    {
      "question": "What areas do you work in?",
      "answer": "We work in education, healthcare, environmental conservation, women empowerment, and community development. Our programs span across rural and urban areas, focusing on underserved communities.",
      "category": "Programs",
      "order": 4,
      "serial": "FAQ-004"
    },
    {
      "question": "How do you ensure transparency in fund utilization?",
      "answer": "We maintain complete transparency through regular financial audits, annual reports, and project updates. All financial statements are published on our website and we provide detailed breakdowns of how donations are utilized.",
      "category": "Transparency",
      "order": 5,
      "serial": "FAQ-005"
    },
    {
      "question": "Can I sponsor a specific project or child?",
      "answer": "Yes, we offer project-specific and child sponsorship programs. You can choose to support a particular initiative or sponsor a child's education. We provide regular updates on the progress of sponsored projects and children.",
      "category": "Sponsorship",
      "order": 6,
      "serial": "FAQ-006"
    }
  ],
