  "about": {
    "title": "About BirdsFly Sangstha",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "__component": "shared.rich-text",
        "body": "## Our Story\n\nBirdsFly Sangstha is a non-governmental organization based in Satkhira District, Bangladesh. We started our journey in 2022, with our office located at Bosundhora Tower, 3rd Floor, Satkhira.\n\n**Contact Us**\n- Phone: 01727009448\n- Email: birdsfly.sangstha@gmail.com\n\n## Our Mission\n\nWe are committed to building resilience, sustainability, and social justice in coastal communities. Our work spans across multiple sectors that directly impact vulnerable populations.\n\n## Our Key Focus Areas\n\n**Climate Change & Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR)**\n- Cyclone preparedness and response\n- Sustainable embankment protection\n- Coastal afforestation\n- Rehabilitation of climate refugees\n\n**Water, Sanitation & Hygiene (WASH)**\n- Saline water purification (RO Plant)\n- Rainwater harvesting\n- Arsenic-free water supply\n- Installation of improved latrines\n\n**Sustainable Agriculture & Food Security**\n- Salt-tolerant rice and vegetable cultivation\n- Cage fish farming\n- Promotion of organic fertilizers\n\n**Public Health & Nutrition**\n- Reproductive health protection for coastal women\n- Maternal and child nutrition programs\n- Prevention of infectious diseases"
      },
      {
        "__component": "shared.quote",
        "title": "BirdsFly Sangstha",
        "body": "We envision coastal communities where every individual has access to clean water, sustainable livelihoods, quality education, and the opportunity to thrive despite climate challenges."
      },
      {
        "__component": "shared.rich-text",
        "body": "## More Focus Areas\n\n**Education & Skill Development**\n- Non-formal education to reduce dropouts\n- ICT training\n- Technical and vocational skill enhancement\n\n**Women Empowerment & Gender Equality**\n- Prevention of child marriage\n- Legal aid for women\n- Small entrepreneurship development for women's self-reliance\n\n**Environment & Biodiversity Conservation**\n- Protection of Sundarbans honey and fish collectors\n- Plastic pollution control\n- Safeguarding local ecosystems\n\n**Child Protection & Rights**\n- Elimination of child labor\n- Rehabilitation of street children\n- Promoting children's mental development\n\n**Governance & Human Rights**\n- Ensuring access to government services\n- Promoting transparency and accountability\n- Protecting land rights\n\n**Youth Development & Volunteerism**\n- Engaging youth in social work\n- Anti-drug campaigns\n- Leadership development\n\n**Technology & Innovation**\n- Use of drones and apps in agriculture\n- E-learning initiatives\n- Expanding digital services to marginalized communities"
      }
    ]
  },
